commit.message: Bump version to 0.98.

Add support for the 'x' set of modes (for Python 3.3+).

Patch originally by Tim Heaney and Vajrasky Kok.

[upstream changeset 5abc04e6579b]

Fix regression in handling of non-bzip2 data at EOF.

[upstream changeset 1f1498fe50e5]

Add test for reading a truncated file.

Patch by Serhiy Storchaka.

[upstream changeset f2f947cdc5fe]
PyPI now has a Python 3.4 trove classifier; add it back in.
Tests now pass on PyPy.
Skip CPython-specific test when running on PyPy.

Fix documentation link in README.rst.

This package isn't just the BZ2File class anymore, so don't link directly to the
documentation for that class.
PyPI doesn't have a Python 3.4 trove classifier yet.
Bump version to 0.95, and update README.rst.

Rewrap docstrings at 72 columns (as per PEP 8).

Also update outdated information in module docstring.

[upstream changeset a61b3faa1c61]

Stylistic tweaks to remove some differences from upstream.

[upstream changeset 8f048c8c855e]

Further optimizations for readline()/readlines().

[upstream changeset 6d7bf512e0c3]

More small read optimizations.

Again, thanks to Serhiy Storchaka for the patch.

[upstream changeset 4258248a44c7]
[upstream changeset e6d872b61c57]

Optimize small reads (including typical readline() usage).

Thanks to Victor Hooi for the bug report, and Serhiy Storchaka for the initial
patch.

[upstream changeset 1a08f4887cff]
[upstream changeset 1b4190d918c9]
[upstream changeset 7252f9f95fe6]

Fix read1()'s handling of pathological input data.

[upstream changeset cdf27a213bd2]

Add test for handling of bytes filenames.

[upstream changeset d129982c063d]
Add multistream-capable decompress() for tests.

Add open() convenience function.

Allows opening in either text or binary mode (unlike BZ2File.__init__).

[upstream changeset 2143386a17a4]

Clarify acceptable values for the mode argument.

[upstream changeset 3235748e6e81]

Make fileobj support easier to use.

[upstream changeset 544e64e18a8a]

Make seekable() check the underlying file object.

This requires some messy introspection, since file objects in 2.x can seek but
do not have a seekable() method.
Add packaging bits.
Fix typo.
Improve README, and convert to reST.
Update docstring of BZ2File.__init__().
Apparently GitHub's online editor is stingy with newlines.
Fix unintentional wildcard expansion in .gitignore.
Fix uses of str.format() under 2.6.
